		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=PraetorFenix&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Kudos on getting a Wurmslayer at your level, first of all.&nbsp;&nbsp;Nice weapon til you hit 45-ish.  Shield is also quite nice, don't sell it if ya don't have to man as I see you have it for sale.<br><br>If you can afford it, get some Electrum Black Sapphire Earrings.  A loss of 2 AC, 6 str is well worth the gain of 40 HP and 50 mana.  I actually wear those at level 59 if you can believe it.<br><br>Neck is nice.<br><br>Face is decent.<br><br>Ditch your hat, get a Deepwater.  Very cheap on my server, I think I sold mine for 350pp and even that took a while to find a buyer.<br><br>Ditch the Fine Plate Pauldron, try and find a Tattered Mantle.  A gain of 2 AC, 20 HP, 20 Disease Resist.  Very cheap upgrade.<br><br>If you can get Velium Fire Opal rings, do it.  A gain of 7 AC, 130 HP (!), for a loss of 8 str and 5 dex.  Relatively cheap upgrade, but a massive one.  MASSIVE.  I was wearing a Velium Fire Opal Ring until just the other day, dey are gud.<br><br>Decent bracers..  Not much for wrist upgrades really.  Deepwater is all ya can really buy. Hero Bracer is excellent.<br><br>For your arms, Deepwater Vambraces are moderately expensive, but are also very nice.  Nothing better than that but Velious quest gear really.<br><br>Chestplate is slick.  Keep it until you can upgrade to Valorium at planes level.<br><br>Cloak of the Icebear as a back upgrade.  You gain cold resist and HP, at the loss of useless dexterity (as you don't use a proccing weapon).<br><br>Get any boots BUT dwarven workboots.  Fine Plate would be an upgrade.  See below for boots advice.<br><br>Waist is nice.  Your strength seems decent, so a Thick Banded Belt isn't really necessary.<br><br>Royal Frosted Velium would be an upgrade for your hands.  If you have any higher level friends who could kill 20 dwarves or so in Icewell Keep (Thurgadin B) for you, you're almost guaranteed some nifty gloves.  And boots too.  I also used both Royal Velium gloves and boots until I upgraded a few weeks ago.<br><br><br>Hope this helps!</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><b>Praetor</b>, 65th Lord Protector of Ascent (Retired)<br><b>Tiresias</b>, 1st Warrior of Asura (Hopefully)</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=995899116906&num=2&page=&post=1&mid=995899116906><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">2 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class6">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
